The tack at index 0 is always the current state.

==== Members

* [[jjdcm_ts]]
//axl_voices axr_member axd_required axt_string
{jjdcm_ts}
is the ISO 8601 timestamp of this snapshot.

* [[jjdcm_state]]
//axl_voices axr_member axd_required axt_enumeration
{jjdcm_state}
is the pace state at this snapshot.
Values:
{jjdpe_rough},
{jjdpe_complete},
{jjdpe_abandoned},
{jjdpe_bridled} (V3-legacy, deprecated).

* [[jjdcm_text]]
//axl_voices axr_member axd_required axt_string
{jjdcm_text}
is the docket text at this snapshot.

* [[jjdcm_silks]]
//axl_voices axr_member axd_required axt_string
{jjdcm_silks}
is the pace display name at this snapshot.
May change across tacks when a pace is relabeled.

* [[jjdcm_basis]]
//axl_voices axr_member axd_required axt_string
{jjdcm_basis}
is the basis commit SHA at the time of this snapshot.
Serialized as `commit` in JSON (Rust field `basis`, serde rename).
Format: 7-character abbreviated SHA, or `0000000` when basis cannot be determined.

* [[jjdcm_direction]]
//axl_voices axr_member axd_optional axt_string
{jjdcm_direction}
is the plan or warrant text.
V3-legacy: present only when state is {jjdpe_bridled}; absent otherwise.
Will become vestigial when {jjdpe_bridled} is removed by ₣An.

=== {jjdyr_table}

[[jjdyr_table]]
//axl_voices axo_entity
{jjdyr_table}::
A structured column layout for formatted output.
Provides single source of truth for headers, widths, and alignment.
Eliminates magic numbers and strings from output code.

==== Members

* [[jjdym_column]]
//axl_voices axr_member
{jjdym_column}
is a column definition with header, width, and alignment.

== Form Expectations

Each AXL category implies an expected
{xref_MCM}
definition form pattern for documents using that category.
During type-scheme linting, these expectations guide validation of definition structure.

* {axc_*} control terms expect
{xref_MCM}
`mcm_form_deflist`
* {axj_structure} definitions expect
{xref_MCM}
`mcm_form_section`
* {axj_field} definitions expect
{xref_MCM}
`mcm_form_bullet` under parent structure
* {axk_premise} definitions expect
{xref_MCM}
`mcm_form_deflist`
* Most other categories expect
{xref_MCM}
`mcm_form_deflist`

These expectations support the
{axl_annotation}

representing discrete actions.
Keyed in JSON by
{jjdt_firemark}.

==== Members

* [[jjdhm_firemark]]
//axl_voices axr_member axd_required
{jjdhm_firemark}
is the
{jjdhr_heat_p}
primary key.
Type:
{jjdt_firemark}.
Implicit from JSON key; not stored as separate field.

* [[jjdhm_silks]]
//axl_voices axr_member axd_required
{jjdhm_silks}
is the
{jjdhr_heat_p}
display name.

{jjdt_coronet}.

==== Members

* [[jjdpm_coronet]]
//axl_voices axr_member axd_required
{jjdpm_coronet}
is the
{jjdpr_pace_p}
globally unique identity.
Type:
{jjdt_coronet}.
Implicit from JSON key; not stored as separate field.

* [[jjdpm_tacks]]
//axl_voices axr_member axd_required axd_repeated
{jjdpm_tacks}
is the ordered history of state snapshots for this
{jjdpr_pace}.
Element type:
{jjdcr_tack}.
Index 0 is the current (most recent) tack;
{jjsgmpt_prepend_tack}
inserts at position zero.

